22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67449383.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Woman%20Faces%20Rs%2033%20Lakh%20Fine%20And%20Prison%20Time%20for%20In-Flight%20Chaos%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20in%20the%20United%20States%20has%20been%20ordered%20by%20a%20court%20to%20pay%20nearly%20%2440%2C000%20to%20American%20Airlines%20as%20compensation%20for%20causing%20a%20disturbance%20with%20a%20crew%20member%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20diversion%20of%20her%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20person%20causing%20trouble%20is%20Cayla%20Farris%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20from%20Hawaii.%20District%20Judge%20Susan%20Brnovich%20ordered%20last%20week%20that%20she%20should%20spend%20a%20bit%20more%20than%20three%20months%20in%20prison.%20After%20that%2C%20she%20has%20to%20be%20supervised%20for%20three%20years.%20Additionally%2C%20she%20has%20to%20give%20%2438%2C952%20to%20American%20Airlines%20to%20cover%20the%20costs%20of%20the%20delays%20she%20caused.%20She%20admitted%20to%20causing%20problems%20with%20the%20flight%20crew%20on%20September%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20all%20happened%20on%20a%20flight%20from%20Phoenix%2C%20Arizona%2C%20to%20Honolulu%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20on%20February%2013%2C%202022.%20While%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20Farris%20threatened%20the%20people%20working%20on%20the%20plane%20and%20other%20passengers%2C%20using%20bad%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20flight%2C%20Farris%20used%20profanity%20and%20threatened%20the%20flight%20crew%20and%20passengers%20on%20board.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20her%20behavior%2C%20the%20flight%20crew%20was%20unable%20to%20continue%20their%20duties.%20The%20captain%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20turn%20the%20plane%20back%20to%20Phoenix.%20For%20passengers%20onboard%2C%20this%20disturbance%20caused%20several%20flights%20to%20be%20rerouted%20to%20Hawaii.%20The%20Federal%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20and%20the%20Phoenix%20Police%20Department%20conducted%20the%20investigation%20in%20this%20case.%20The%20United%20States%20Attorney's%20Office%2C%20District%20of%20Arizona%2C%20Phoenix%2C%20handled%20the%20prosecution%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-az%2Fpr%2Fwoman-ordered-pay-over-38000-restitution-interference-flight-crew-hawaii-bound-flight%5C%22%3EUS%20Attorney's%20Office%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20Arizona%20said%20in%20a%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700222880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-11%2Ft931lklk_american-airlines-reuters_625x300_15_November_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-woman-faces-rs-33-lakh-fine-and-prison-time-for-in-flight-chaos-4582752%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Hawaiian%20woman%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%20pay%20almost%20%2440%2C000%20in%20restitution%20to%20American%20Airlines%20after%20she%20interfered%20with%20a%20crew%20member%20and%20forced%20her%20flight%20to%20be%20diverted.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-woman-faces-rs-33-lakh-fine-and-prison-time-for-in-flight-chaos-4582752%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-woman-faces-rs-33-lakh-fine-and-prison-time-for-in-flight-chaos-4582752%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-woman-faces-rs-33-lakh-fine-and-prison-time-for-in-flight-chaos-4582752%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Six%20memorable%20India-Australia%20ODI%20matches%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700222516000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105293293%2Cimgsize-46592.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Ficc-world-cup%2Fnews%2Fdesert-storm-to-steve-smith-revenge-six-memorable-india-australia-odi-matches%2Farticleshow%2F105293165.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%2C%20unbeaten%20throughout%20the%20tournament%2C%20will%20face%20the%20five-time%20champions%20Australia%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%20final%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%20hosted%20in%20the%20world's%20largest%20cricket%20stadium%2C%20on%20Sunday.%20Here's%20a%20look%20at%20six%20unforgettable%20encounters%20between%20the%20two%20powerhouses%20of%20cricket.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Misguided%20Mega-Projects%20Threaten%20to%20Devastate%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17154151%2Fmirante-andaman-ferry.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ET%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands%2C%20jointly%20administered%20as%20a%20Union%20Territory%20of%20India%2C%20form%20two%20lush%20green%20archipelagos%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20south%20of%20Myanmar%20and%20west%20of%20Thailand%20and%20Malaysia.%20The%20NITI%20Aayog%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20top%20public-policy%20think%20tank%2C%20has%20since%202019%20promoted%20a%20pair%20of%20development%20mega-projects%20here%20which%20promise%20to%20transform%20%E2%80%93%20or%20devastate%20%E2%80%93%20the%20southernmost%20islands%20in%20each%20chain%2C%20Little%20Andaman%20and%20Great%20Nicobar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELittle%20Andaman%20was%20first%20in%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20sights%2C%20but%20the%20think%20tank%E2%80%99s%20mega-project%20for%20that%20island%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20suspended%20since%202021%2C%20with%20news%20updates%20on%20the%20project%20trickling%20out%20and%20without%20any%20formal%20announcement%20or%20explanation.%20Instead%2C%20the%20project%20on%20Great%20Nicobar%20Island%20%E2%80%93%20with%20an%20international%20container%20vessel%20transshipment%20port%2C%20and%20a%20new%20city%20and%20airport%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20%E2%80%9Cfast-tracked%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20construction%20bids%20underway%20as%20of%20April%202023%20(although%20construction%20has%20been%20temporarily%20halted%20due%20to%20a%20case%20before%20the%20National%20Green%20Tribunal).%20The%20NITI%20Aayog%20and%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands%20Integrated%20Development%20Corporation%2C%20a%20body%20formed%20to%20execute%20the%20projects%2C%20have%20shunned%20transparency%20on%20the%20funding%20sources%20for%20the%20work%2C%20but%20the%20Great%20Nicobar%20scheme%20has%20been%20estimated%20to%20cost%20720%20billion%20Indian%20rupees%2C%20or%20nearly%20USD%209%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20mega-projects%20have%20already%20challenged%20the%20land%20rights%20of%20the%20Onge%2C%20Shompen%20and%20Nicobarese%20indigenous%20people%2C%20seen%20a%20major%20sea%20turtle%20sanctuary%20denotified%20and%20set%20in%20motion%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccompensatory%E2%80%9D%20bait-and-switch%20involving%20a%20jungle%20safari%20park%202400%20kilometres%20away.%20Despite%20urgent%20warnings%20of%20further%20environmental%20damage%2C%20seismic%20risks%20and%20dire%20human-rights%20implications%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20is%20plunging%20ahead%20with%20its%20plans%20to%20commercialise%2C%20industrialise%20and%20militarise%20the%20islands%E2%80%99%20coastlines%2C%20reefs%20and%20forests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fcolleges-in-andaman-nicobar-to-come-under-one-deemed-university-nsui-launches-protest%5C%22%3EColleges%20in%20Andaman%20Nicobar%20to%20Come%20Under%20One%20Deemed%20University%2C%20NSUI%20Launches%20Protest%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBig%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%E2%80%9D%20on%20Little%20Andaman%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Onges%20of%20Little%20Andaman%20are%20one%20of%20the%20several%20distinct%20groups%20of%20surviving%20indigenous%20peoples%20of%20the%20Andaman%20Islands.%20DNA%20studies%20estimate%20the%20arrival%20of%20their%20ancestors%20on%20the%20islands%20to%20date%20to%20around%2018%2C000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20still%20largely%20uncontacted%20Sentinelese%20to%20their%20north%20in%20the%20Andaman%20archipelago%20(who%20in%202018%20killed%20an%20American%20attempting%20to%20evangelise%20them)%2C%20the%20Onges%20are%20all%20too%20familiar%20with%20schemes%20to%20assimilate%2C%20modernise%20or%20exploit%20them.%20For%20centuries%2C%20Onges%20fiercely%20fended%20off%20slave%20traders%20and%20raided%20wrecked%20ships%20that%20came%20to%20be%20in%20their%20waters.%20In%201901%2C%20the%20Onge%20population%20was%20estimated%20at%20around%20625%20people.%20In%20the%201960s%20and%201970s%2C%20Indian%20government%20agents%20took%20charge%20of%20Little%20Andaman%20and%20began%20bringing%20over%20settlers%20from%20mainland%20India.%20As%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%202011%20census%2C%20the%20total%20population%20of%20Little%20Andaman%20was%20roughly%2019%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F10132937%2F9463871286_055b9eee97_b.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F10132937%2F9463871286_055b9eee97_b.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F10132937%2F9463871286_055b9eee97_b-300x138.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-459699%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22470%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands.%20Photo%3A%20Steve%20Hoge%2FFlickr%2C%20CC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%202004%20tsunami%2C%20the%20government%20moved%20the%20Onges%20to%20reserves%20where%20they%20were%20housed%20in%20asbestos-roofed%20wooden%20cabins.%20As%20I%20wrote%20in%20my%202014%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Wind%20in%20the%20Bamboo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20looked%20at%20the%20past%20and%20present%20of%20indigenous%20Asian%20peoples%20categorised%20by%20scientific%20racism%20as%20%E2%80%9CNegritos%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Onges%20%E2%80%9Csuffered%20captivity%20depression%2C%20sexual%20abuse%20by%20government%20workers%2C%20and%20alcohol%20dependence%20when%20they%20were%20confined%20to%20the%20two%20reserves%20on%20separate%20ends%20of%20the%20island.%E2%80%9D%20Now%2C%20the%20Onge%20population%20numbers%20only%20about%20125%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20was%20founded%20in%202015%20under%20India%E2%80%99s%20current%20prime%20minister%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20as%20a%20replacement%20for%20the%20Planning%20Commission%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20main%20planning%20organ%20since%20the%201950s.%20In%20January%202021%2C%20a%20NITI%20Aayog%20%E2%80%98Vision%20Document%E2%80%99%20describing%20the%20development%20of%20mega-projects%20for%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands%20was%20revealed%20in%20the%20press.%20Like%20with%20pretty%20much%20every%20government%20or%20business%20document%20that%20has%20ever%20had%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cvision%E2%80%9D%20in%20its%20title%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20plans%20were%20self-justifying%20and%20speculative.%20The%20document%20proposed%20that%20%E2%80%9CLittle%20Andaman%3A%20The%20Perfect%20Paradise%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20developed%20%E2%80%9Cto%20compete%20with%20global%20cities%20like%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20Singapore%20or%20Dubai.%E2%80%9D%20The%20island%20would%20sprout%20an%20%E2%80%9CAerocity%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20%E2%80%9CMedicity%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20financial%20district%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9CPlug%20%26amp%3B%20Play%20office%20Complex.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F643377%2Fwho-is-the-great-nicobar-holistic-development-project-really-for%2F%5C%22%3EWho%20Is%20the%20Great%20Nicobar%20%E2%80%98Holistic%20Development%E2%80%99%20Project%20Really%20For%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3Cins%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20a%20new%20international%20airport%2C%20there%20would%20be%20a%20second%20airstrip%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20private%20and%20direct%20access%20to%20the%20Super%20Luxurious%20Forest%20resorts.%E2%80%9D%20Leisure%20pursuits%20might%20include%20an%20%E2%80%9CUnderwater%20Safari%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20%E2%80%9CWildlife%20Safari%E2%80%9D%20and%20even%20a%20%E2%80%9CRiver%20Safari%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20although%20there%20is%20no%20river%20on%20the%20island.%20This%2C%20and%20the%20mention%20of%20nonexistent%20%E2%80%9Cmountains%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20Little%20Andaman%20has%20a%20maximum%20elevation%20of%20183%20metres%20%E2%80%93%20indicated%20that%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20authors%20had%20likely%20never%20so%20much%20as%20been%20to%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20report%E2%80%99s%20section%20titled%20%E2%80%9CInvestment%20Potential%3A%20Entertainment%E2%80%9D%20was%20illustrated%20with%20a%20photo%20of%20scantily%20dressed%20persons%20interacting%20with%20male%20tourists%20on%20Bangkok%E2%80%99s%20notorious%20Soi%20Cowboy%2C%20with%20the%20distinctive%20neon%20sign%20of%20The%20Dollhouse%20bar%20and%20a%20child%20flower-seller%20clearly%20visible.%20Suddenly%2C%20the%20vision%20was%20not%20Singapore%20anymore.%20On%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20respectability%20scale%2C%20a%20section%20on%20%E2%80%9CHealthcare%20%26amp%3B%20Wellness%E2%80%9D%20used%20a%20photo%20of%20the%20entrance%20to%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%2C%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20introduction%20to%20its%20report%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20presence%20of%20indigenous%20tribes%20and%20concerns%20for%20their%20welfare%20has%20been%20a%20key%20factor%20challenging%20island%20development.%E2%80%9D%20Describing%20the%20Onges%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprimitive%20tribal%20group%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Vision%20Document%E2%80%99%20listed%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpresence%20of%20the%20Tribal%20Reserve%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ckey%20constraint%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20overcome.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20required%2C%20the%20tribals%20can%20be%20relocated%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20island%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20casually%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202021%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20requested%20that%207733%20square%20kilometres%20of%20land%20in%20the%20Onge%20Tribal%20Reserve%20be%20%E2%80%9Cdenotified%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20to%20be%20cut%20out%20from%20the%20reserve%20and%20stripped%20of%20protected%20status%20%E2%80%93%20to%20enable%20%E2%80%9CPhase%20I%E2%80%9D%20development.%20This%20was%20accompanied%20with%20a%20comment%20that%20the%20Onges%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9Ctraditional%20lifestyles%20are%20out%20of%20step%20with%20the%20march%20of%20history.%E2%80%9D%20The%20NITI%20Aayog%20also%20planned%20to%20request%20the%20denotification%20of%20an%20additional%20138%20square%20kilometres%20of%20land%20and%20to%20acquire%2022%20square%20kilometres%20of%20the%20Onges%E2%80%99%20offshore%20tribal%20reserve%20%E2%80%93%20amounting%20to%2057%20percent%20of%20its%20total%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F11164305%2FRain_over_Great_Nicobar_Biosphere_Reserve.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F11164305%2FRain_over_Great_Nicobar_Biosphere_Reserve.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F11164305%2FRain_over_Great_Nicobar_Biosphere_Reserve-300x225.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-606963%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EView%20of%20rainfall%20over%20the%20forest%20and%20adjacent%20sea%20from%20a%20watchtower%20of%20the%20Great%20Nicobar%20Biosphere%20Reserve%2C%20Great%20Nicobar%20Island%2C%202016.%20Photo%3A%20Prasun%20Goswami%2FWikimedia%20Commons%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20view%20of%20the%20Onge%20perpetuates%20a%20terrible%20legacy%20of%20outsiders%20considering%20them%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cprimitive%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CPaleolithic%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20even%20more%20pejorative%20%E2%80%9Csavages%E2%80%9D.%20This%20dates%20to%20at%20least%20the%20colonial%20period%2C%20but%20the%20end%20of%20colonialism%20has%20done%20nothing%20to%20change%20the%20Indian%20state%E2%80%99s%20view.%20The%20islands%E2%80%99%20Black%20Indigenous%20Asians%20are%20widely%20assumed%20to%20be%20relics%20of%20the%20distant%20past%20and%20have%20been%20treated%2C%20literally%2C%20as%20attractions%20in%20a%20human%20safari%2C%20with%20buses%20full%20of%20gawping%20outsiders%20rolling%20through%20indigenous%20reserves.%20Their%20choices%20about%20contact%20with%20the%20outside%20world%20have%20always%20been%2C%20and%20continue%20to%20be%2C%20conveniently%20ignored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20while%20researching%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Wind%20in%20the%20Bamboo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20put%20my%20history%20books%20and%20DNA-science%20papers%20aside%20to%20visit%20the%20Andaman%20Islands.%20There%2C%20I%20met%20Samir%20Acharya%2C%20a%20legendary%20troublemaker%20who%20had%20defeated%20the%20islands%E2%80%99%20logging%20industry.%20His%20Society%20for%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Ecology%20championed%20the%20land%20rights%20of%20the%20Onges%20and%20the%20Jarawas%2C%20another%20local%20indigenous%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Little%20Andaman%2C%20I%20caught%20a%20bus%20to%20a%20beach%20called%20Butler%20Bay%2C%20where%20green%20parakeets%20sparkled%20in%20the%20trees%20and%20a%20few%20Aussie%20surfers%20were%20camped%20near%20a%20%E2%80%9Cworld-class%20left-hand%20break.%E2%80%9D%20Nearby%2C%20two%20local%20men%2C%20one%20an%20Onge%2C%20were%20at%20work%20carrying%20wooden%20posts.%20Butler%20Bay%20is%20the%20location%20for%20the%20proposed%20Financial%20District%20and%20Aerocity%20in%20the%20alternate%20reality%20of%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Vision%20Document%E2%80%99.%20This%20was%20part%20of%20the%20first%20portion%20of%20the%20Onge%20Tribal%20Reserve%20that%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20sought%20to%20denotify%20in%20February%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F683666%2Fniti-aayog-considers-discontinuing-key-report-on-water-management%2F%5C%22%3ENITI%20Aayog%20Considers%20Discontinuing%20Key%20Report%20on%20Water%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultation%20with%20the%20Onges%20and%20settlers%20of%20Little%20Andaman%20was%20conspicuously%20missing%20from%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20plans.%20This%20fit%20a%20long-standing%20pattern%3A%20rather%20than%20listening%20to%20the%20islanders%2C%20Indian%20government%20officials%20have%20long%20served%20as%20gatekeepers%20preventing%20the%20Onges%20and%20others%20from%20complaining%20to%20outsiders.%20The%20Onge%20reserve%20at%20Dugong%20Creek%20lacks%20cellphone%20service%20and%20in-person%20access%20is%20tightly%20controlled.%20Sophie%20Grig%20of%20Survival%20International%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20advocates%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20indigenous%20Andaman%20islanders%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20appear%20that%20the%20free%2C%20prior%20and%20informed%20consent%20of%20the%20Onge%20was%20neither%20sought%20nor%20given%20for%20this%20change%20to%20their%20reserve.%20This%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20their%20rights%20under%20international%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20denotification%20effort%20in%20Little%20Andaman%20may%20have%20set%20a%20precedent%20for%20other%20official%20dealings%20with%20indigenous%20peoples%20of%20the%20Andaman%20Islands%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20Jarawas%2C%20who%20constantly%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20encroachment%20on%20their%20lands%2C%20and%20even%20the%20Sentinelese%2C%20who%20continue%20to%20defend%20themselves%20against%20outsiders.%20The%20approach%20seems%20to%20involve%20treating%20them%20as%20obstructions%20to%20progress%2C%20as%20historical%20relics%20without%20a%20say%20in%20the%20future%20of%20their%20islands%2C%20to%20be%20uprooted%20and%20displaced%20at%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CSingapore%E2%80%9D%20on%20Great%20Nicobar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20has%20not%20moved%20forward%20with%20its%20Little%20Andaman%20project%20since%202021.%20Instead%2C%20by%20early%202022%2C%20it%20pivoted%20to%20activating%20its%20plan%20for%20a%20transshipment%20port%20designed%20to%20host%20massive%20container%20vessels%20on%20Great%20Nicobar%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20island%20in%20the%20Nicobars%2C%20currently%20sparsely%20populated%20and%20thickly%20forested%20across%20its%20921%20square%20kilometres.%20Despite%20the%20improbability%20of%20this%20new%20port%20being%20able%20to%20compete%20with%20regional%20transshipment%20behemoths%20such%20as%20Singapore%2C%20Port%20Klang%20in%20Malaysia%20and%20Colombo%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20or%20even%20with%20new%20port%20facilities%20on%20the%20Indian%20mainland%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20is%20pressing%20ahead.%20Its%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20Singapore%E2%80%9D%20dream%20for%20Great%20Nicobar%20includes%20not%20just%20the%20port%2C%20but%20also%20a%20sprawling%20city%2C%20power%20plants%20and%20an%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20airport%20would%20be%20partly%20for%20military%20use%2C%20tying%20the%20whole%20project%20to%20national%20security.%20This%20aspect%20has%20been%20used%20to%20justify%20secrecy%20about%20deforestation%20related%20to%20the%20planned%20airport.%20An%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20base%20already%20exists%20on%20another%20island%20of%20the%20archipelago%2C%20Car%20Nicobar%2C%20and%20the%20Nicobars%20have%20navy%20port%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20shipping%20stopover%20during%20British%20colonial%20times%2C%20the%20Nicobars%20have%20been%20largely%20closed%20to%20outside%20commercial%20ventures%20since%20India%20gained%20independence%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20protecting%20the%20indigenous%20people.%20Even%20so%2C%20there%20was%20earlier%20some%20rubber%20cultivation%20on%20the%20islands%20and%20resettlement%20of%20people%20from%20mainland%20India.%20From%201956%20to%202018%2C%20both%20international%20and%20domestic%20tourists%20were%20barred%20from%20the%20Nicobar%20Islands.%20But%20now%2C%20as%20with%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20for%20Little%20Andaman%2C%20the%20disruptive%20Great%20Nicobar%20scheme%20envisions%20infrastructure%20for%20mass%20tourism%20on%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fconstitutional-conduct-group-great-nicobar-project%5C%22%3EFormer%20Civil%20Servants%20Ask%20President%20to%20Halt%20%E2%80%98%20Undesirable%20Development%E2%80%99%20of%20Great%20Nicobar%20Island%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20proposed%20transshipment%20port%20and%20new%20city%20are%20placed%20squarely%20in%20a%20zone%20with%20significant%20tsunami%20and%20earthquake%20dangers.%20The%202004%20Indian%20Ocean%20tsunami%20hit%20the%20Nicobars%20severely%2C%20killing%20thousands.%20Great%20Nicobar%2C%20located%20along%20an%20active%20subduction%20system%20and%20near%20multiple%20geological%20fault%20lines%2C%20is%20very%20seismically%20unstable%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%2044%20earthquakes%20per%20year.%20Writing%20about%20the%20project%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFrontline%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%20January%202023%2C%20the%20scientists%20Janki%20Andharia%2C%20V%20Ramesh%20and%20Ravinder%20Dhiman%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CFollowing%20building%20codes%20is%20one%20thing%2C%20but%20going%20ahead%20and%20building%20on%20a%20fault%20line%20is%20reckless.%E2%80%9D%20Great%20Nicobar%20is%20also%20extremely%20vulnerable%20to%20cyclonic%20storms%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20global%20climate%20crisis%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20rising%20sea%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20indigenous%20peoples%20of%20the%20Nicobar%20Islands%20are%20the%20Nicobarese%20and%20Shompens.%20Of%20Great%20Nicobar%E2%80%99s%20population%20of%20approximately%208500%20people%2C%20about%20a%20thousand%20are%20Nicobarese%20and%20an%20estimated%20245%20are%20Shompens%2C%20with%20the%20rest%20being%20settlers%20from%20mainland%20India%20and%20their%20descendants.%20The%20Nicobarese%2C%20who%20live%20on%20several%20islands%20in%20the%20archipelago%2C%20speak%20Austroasiatic%20languages.%20Their%20culture%20includes%20traditional%20domed-thatch%20%E2%80%9Cbeehive%E2%80%9D%20houses%2C%20carved%20effigies%20and%20a%20form%20of%20Christian%E2%80%93Animist%20syncretism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reclusive%20people%20known%20to%20outsiders%20as%20Shompens%20live%20only%20on%20Great%20Nicobar%2C%20speak%20their%20own%20language%20and%20are%20primarily%20forest%20foragers.%20The%20hilly%20inland%20region%20they%20roam%20is%20delineated%20by%20several%20rivers%20and%20streams.%20Like%20the%20indigenous%20peoples%20of%20the%20Andamans%20(to%20whom%20they%20are%20not%20related)%2C%20Shompens%20have%20been%20derided%20as%20marauding%20%E2%80%9Csavages%E2%80%9D.%20They%20limit%20contact%20with%20outsiders%20and%20are%20considered%20forest%20guardians%20by%20the%20Nicobarese%2C%20who%20traditionally%20ask%20their%20permission%20before%20felling%20trees.%20Parts%20of%20the%20island%20where%20the%20Shompens%20currently%20live%20are%20included%20in%20a%20UNESCO%20Biosphere%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F11153514%2F8543143641_3bbf62743e_b.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F11153514%2F8543143641_3bbf62743e_b.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F11153514%2F8543143641_3bbf62743e_b-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-453941%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20forest%20in%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands.%20Photo%3A%20Flickr%2F%20Neelima%20V%20CC%20BY%20NC%20ND%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%202004%20tsunami%2C%20many%20Nicobarese%20were%20relocated%20from%20their%20villages%20by%20the%20government%20as%20part%20of%20relief%20operations.%20Despite%20repeated%20requests%20to%20re-inhabit%20their%20original%20land%2C%20they%20were%20never%20allowed%20to%20return.%20A%20few%20Shompens%20were%20also%20relocated%20with%20the%20Nicobarese%2C%20among%20them%20a%20young%20man%20named%20Kakein%20who%2C%20removed%20from%20his%20culture%20and%20language%20group%2C%20took%20his%20own%20life%20in%202018.%20A%20group%20of%20anthropologists%20and%20other%20experts%20made%20a%20short%20film%20about%20Great%20Nicobar%20in%202019%2C%20in%20which%20one%20anthropologist%20asked%20a%20Shompen%20man%20for%20his%20response%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%E2%80%9D.%20His%20reply%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CDo%20not%20come%20near%20our%20hills.%20Do%20not%20clear%20hills.%20Do%20not%20climb%20our%20hills.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nicobarese%20and%20coastal%20settlers%20of%20Great%20Nicobar%20have%20long%20expressed%20a%20desire%20for%20basic%20improvements%20in%20healthcare%2C%20education%20and%20inter-island%20connectivity.%20What%20they%20have%20not%20been%20asking%20for%20is%20mass%20tourism%20or%20development%20mega-projects.%20In%202022%2C%20representatives%20of%20relocated%20Nicobarese%20and%20Shompens%20yet%20again%20sent%20formal%20appeals%20to%20the%20government%20for%20the%20return%20of%20their%20lands%20and%20decried%20the%20deterioration%20of%20their%20health%20and%20culture%20due%20to%20prolonged%20displacement.%20The%20researcher%20Ajay%20Saini%2C%20writing%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFrontline%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0quoted%20a%20displaced%20Nicobarese%2C%20Paul%20Joora%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20miss%20our%20villages%2C%20but%20they%20will%20also%20be%20missing%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EE%20A%20S%20Sarma%2C%20a%20retired%20Indian%20government%20official%2C%20has%20sent%20several%20letters%20of%20concern%20to%20government%20agencies%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20stressing%20the%20need%20to%20protect%20the%20Nicobarese%20and%20Shompens%20and%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20latter%20are%20officially%20designated%20as%20a%20Particularly%20Vulnerable%20Tribal%20Group.%20Sarma%20has%20noted%20that%20the%20project%20intends%20to%20eventually%20settle%20350%2C000%20people%20on%20Great%20Nicobar%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Chuge%20influx%20of%20outsiders%2C%20whose%20presence%20would%20impact%20the%20Tribal%20Reserve%20and%20hurt%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20local%20tribal%20groups.%E2%80%9D%20Most%20of%20Great%20Nicobar%20is%20a%20designated%20tribal%20reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20government%20initially%20gained%20a%20No%20Objection%20Certificate%20for%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20project%20from%20the%20Tribal%20Council%20of%20Great%20Nicobar.%20This%20was%20done%20in%20August%202022%2C%20but%20within%20months%20the%20Tribal%20Council%20withdrew%20its%20consent%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20had%20been%20misled%20about%20the%20project%E2%80%99s%20diversion%20of%20a%20swathe%20of%20ancestral%20domain%20lands%2C%20which%20were%20to%20be%20treated%20as%20%E2%80%9Cvacant%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20the%20project.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20express%20our%20strong%20disagreement%20to%20this%20decision%20and%20demand%20that%20the%20forest%20clearance%20and%20the%20denotification%20of%20our%20Tribal%20Reserve%20be%20revoked%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20council%E2%80%99s%20letter%20of%20withdrawal%20said.%20Ajay%20Saini%20quoted%20a%20Nicobarese%20village%20leader%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%20lied%20to%20us%20in%20the%20public%20hearing.%20The%20project%20will%20eat%20several%20of%20our%20pre-tsunami%20villages.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDamage%20done%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreat%20Nicobar%E2%80%99s%20Galathea%20Bay%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary%20is%20a%20crucial%20nesting%20area%20for%20leatherback%20sea%20turtles.%20The%20highly%20biodiverse%20island%20is%20also%20the%20habitat%20of%20Nicobar%20long-tailed%20macaques%2C%20Nicobar%20treeshrews%2C%20Nicobar%20scops%20owls%2C%20Nicobar%20pigeons%2C%20and%20a%20large%20bird%20called%20the%20Nicobar%20megapode.%20Now%2C%20these%20species%20and%20more%20are%20in%20jeopardy%20from%20the%20immense%20footprint%20of%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20mega-project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20way%20for%20the%20port%2C%20in%20early%202021%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20was%20able%20to%20have%20the%20Galathea%20Bay%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary%20denotified%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20Standing%20Committee%20of%20the%20National%20Board%20for%20Wildlife.%20This%20was%20accompanied%20by%20ineffectual%20suggestions%20for%20mitigation%20of%20the%20environmental%20impact%2C%20such%20as%20the%20use%20of%20%E2%80%9CEcological%20Marker%20Buoys.%E2%80%9D%20If%20the%20project%20comes%20to%20fruition%2C%20Galathea%20Bay%E2%80%99s%20nesting%20beaches%2C%20used%20by%20hundreds%20of%20leatherback%20turtles%2C%20would%20be%20irremediably%20blocked%20by%20piers%20and%20breakwaters.%20The%20marine%20environment%20surrounding%20Great%20Nicobar%20would%20also%20be%20disrupted%20by%20the%20arrival%20of%20massive%20container%20ships.%20In%20addition%2C%20construction%20of%20the%20port%20and%20city%2C%20intended%20to%20stretch%20over%20decades%20and%20consume%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20entire%20southeast%20coast%2C%20would%20also%20destroy%20mangrove%20forests%20and%20coral%20reefs%20that%20act%20as%20essential%20storm%20barriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20procedure%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20commissioned%20an%20Environmental%20Impact%20Assessment%20(EIA)%20on%20the%20project%20from%20a%20consulting%20firm%2C%20Vimta%20Labs.%20In%202022%2C%20Vimta%20produced%20a%20brief%20report%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20project.%20Among%20many%20other%20flaws%2C%20this%20EIA%20underreported%20the%20extent%20of%20Great%20Nicobar%E2%80%99s%20Tribal%20Reserve%20Area%20by%20over%20100%20square%20kilometres.%20Confusingly%2C%20Vimta%E2%80%99s%20EIA%20generally%20used%20%E2%80%9CNicobaries%E2%80%9D%20to%20refer%20to%20islanders%20of%20all%20ethnicities%2C%20but%20also%20frequently%20used%20%E2%80%9CNicobaries%E2%80%9D%20to%20refer%20specifically%20to%20the%20Nicobarese%20indigenous%20people.%20The%20document%20stated%20in%20one%20place%20that%20on%20Great%20Nicobar%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctotal%20Nicobaries%20Population%20is%20860%20and%20household%20are%20230%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20asserted%20elsewhere%20of%20the%20Nicobarese%20and%20Shompens%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctheir%20present%20population%20is%201094%20and%20237%20respectively.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EIA%20was%20padded%20out%20with%20ethnographic%20descriptions%20of%20the%20Shompens%20and%20Nicobarese%20lifted%20nearly%20verbatim%20from%20Wikipedia%20pages.%20It%20also%20included%20numerous%20pieces%20of%20outdated%20or%20misleading%20information.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20document%20stated%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CNicobarese%20are%20headed%20by%20a%20chief%20called%20%E2%80%98Rani%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98queen%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20not%20the%20case%20in%20Great%20Nicobar%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9CNo%20agriculture%20is%20being%20practiced%E2%80%9D%20by%20%E2%80%9CNicobaries%E2%80%9D%2C%20ignoring%20their%20orchards%20and%20vegetable%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVimta%E2%80%99s%20EIA%20featured%20a%20frightening%20depiction%20of%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20topography%20and%20ecosystems%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20hills%20are%20steep%2C%20slippery%20and%20totally%20covered%20by%20multi-storeyed%20vegetation.%20Whenever%20we%20could%20gain%20entry%20through%20some%20opening%20into%20the%20dense%2Fthick%20forest%2C%20visibility%20was%20poor%3B%20humidity%20was%20high%3B%20soil%20was%20wet%20and%20slippery%20%E2%80%A6%20Added%20to%20the%20problem%20was%20biting%20insects%20including%20mosquitoes.%E2%80%9D%20The%20document%20also%20called%20Great%20Nicobar%E2%80%99s%20long-tailed%20macaques%2C%20a%20vulnerable%20subspecies%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmenace%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20advised%20relocating%20them%20to%20other%20islands.%20The%20EIA%20also%20suggested%20relocating%20crocodiles%20from%20the%20project%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20462px)%2085vw%2C%20462px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F09155800%2F20495592109_bbb72b8951_c.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F09155800%2F20495592109_bbb72b8951_c.jpg%20575w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F09155800%2F20495592109_bbb72b8951_c-216x300.jpg%20216w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-643396%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22643%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20main%20areas%20of%20tropical%20rain%20forest%20in%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands.%20Photo%3A%20Internet%20Archive%20Book%20Images%2FFlickr.%20Public%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20asserted%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20western%20flank%20of%20the%20Galathea%20beach%20where%20the%20leatherback%20turtle%20nests%2C%20is%20about%201.5%20km%20from%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20power%20plant%20boundary%20and%20is%20separated%20by%20sporadic%20dense%20for%20%5Bsic%5D%20forest%20and%20riverine%20vegetation.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20power%20plant%20construction%20will%20have%20no%20deleterious%20impact%20on%20the%20nesting%20of%20the%20leatherback%20turtles.%E2%80%9D%20This%20showed%20a%20stunning%20disregard%20for%20the%20fragility%20of%20sea%20turtle%20nesting%20sites%2C%20which%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20erosion%20and%20disruption%20of%20access%20as%20well%20as%20noise%20and%20light%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202022%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20Forest%20Advisory%20Committee%20approved%20the%20obliteration%20of%20130%20square%20kilometres%20of%20primary%20forest%20on%20Great%20Nicobar%20for%20the%20project%2C%20conditional%20on%20%E2%80%9Ccompensatory%20afforestation.%E2%80%9D%20Astoundingly%2C%20this%20was%20to%20occur%202400%20kilometres%20away%20in%20Haryana%2C%20on%20the%20Indian%20mainland%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20new%20%E2%80%9Cjungle%E2%80%9D%20zoo%2C%20billed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20curated%20safari.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Ports%2C%20Shipping%20and%20Waterways%2C%20and%20Vimta%20Labs%20had%20not%20responded%20to%20emailed%20questions%20about%20the%20development%20projects%20at%20the%20time%20this%20article%20was%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnvironmentalists%20have%20challenged%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20Great%20Nicobar%20project%20before%20India%E2%80%99s%20National%20Green%20Tribunal.%20In%20April%202023%2C%20the%20tribunal%20ruled%20that%20the%20project%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20call%20for%20interference%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20has%20%E2%80%9Cgreat%20significance%20not%20only%20for%20economic%20development%20of%20the%20island%20and%20surrounding%20areas%20of%20strategic%20location%20but%20also%20for%20defence%20and%20national%20security.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%20placed%20a%20temporary%20hold%20on%20%E2%80%9Cirreversible%E2%80%9D%20steps%20involving%20%E2%80%9Cenvironmental%20clearance%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20project%20so%20a%20special%20committee%20could%20examine%20its%20effects%20on%20coral%20reefs%2C%20the%20possible%20insufficiencies%20in%20its%20impact%20assessments%2C%20and%20the%20very%20notion%20of%20building%20a%20port%20in%20an%20official%20Coastal%20Regulation%20Zone%20where%20construction%20is%20not%20allowed.%20But%20this%20committee%20did%20not%20appear%20independent%20or%20impartial%2C%20as%20it%20was%20to%20include%20one%20member%20nominated%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Ports%2C%20Shipping%20and%20Waterways%2C%20another%20selected%20by%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20and%20others%20from%20bodies%20which%20have%20already%20given%20their%20support%20to%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20journalists%2C%20academics%2C%20scientists%20and%20activists%20who%20care%20deeply%20about%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands%20have%20been%20sounding%20alarms%20about%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20plans%20for%20many%20years%20now.%20A%20few%20politicians%20have%20joined%20them%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20overcome%20the%20fortress%20mentality%20or%20at-all-costs%20approach%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%E2%80%9D%20that%20characterises%20the%20government%20of%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Access%20to%20the%20Nicobarese%20to%20gauge%20their%20opinions%20is%20very%20limited%2C%20and%20this%20is%20even%20more%20the%20case%20for%20the%20Onges%20and%20Shompens%2C%20whose%20protective%20isolation%20ironically%20deprives%20them%20of%20a%20say%20in%20the%20disposal%20of%20their%20islands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20was%20close-mouthed%20throughout%20the%20process%20of%20obtaining%20the%20necessary%20permissions%20for%20the%20project%2C%20and%20even%20denied%20the%20existence%20of%20its%20original%20%E2%80%98Vision%20Document%E2%80%99%20in%20response%20to%20Right%20to%20Information%20applications.%20The%20Great%20Nicobar%20port%20project%20is%20now%20moving%20forward%20under%20the%20watch%20of%20Sarbananda%20Sonowal%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20minister%20for%20ports%2C%20shipping%20and%20waterways.%20In%20March%202023%2C%20he%20told%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20no%20second%20thoughts%20on%20the%20project.%20The%20expression%20of%20interest%20round%20has%20been%20completed%2C%20and%20several%20parties%20have%20shown%20interest.%20It%20is%20true%20that%20different%20stakeholders%20have%20raised%20environmental%20concerns%2C%20but%20those%20have%20been%20clearly%20addressed.%E2%80%9D%20The%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENicobar%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20digital%20publication%20that%20has%20been%20supportive%20of%20the%20project%2C%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20expressions%20of%20interest%20submitted%20by%20ten%20companies%20for%20Phase%20I%20of%20the%20port%20project%20were%20%E2%80%9Ca%20tight%20slap%20on%20the%20rumour%20mongers%20and%20haters%E2%80%9D%20standing%20against%20the%20project%2C%20and%20has%20also%20labeled%20the%20opposition%20to%20the%20port%20a%20%E2%80%9Csmear%20campaign.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20grandest%20plans%20never%20materialise%2C%20immense%20and%20irremediable%20damage%20can%20be%20done%20just%20by%20Phase%20I%20preparations.%20This%20includes%20deforestation%2C%20pollution%2C%20habitat%20disruption%2C%20loss%20of%20ancestral%20land%20rights%20and%20more.%20It%20will%20take%20grim%20determination%2C%20relentless%20legal%20action%20and%20massive%20amplification%20of%20islanders%E2%80%99%20opposition%20to%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20defeat%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20mega-projects%20before%20they%20cause%20enormous%20environmental%2C%20social%20and%20cultural%20ruin%20in%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.himalmag.com%2Fniti-aayog-mega-projects-threaten-to-devastate-andaman-nicobar-islands%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22h