ia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-1-1699622951-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-1-1699622951-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-1-1699622951-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-334027%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIn%201945%2C%20Asha%20became%20a%20lieutenant%20of%20the%20Rani%20of%20Jhansi%20Regiment%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Army.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EKadam%20Kadam%20Badhaye%20Ja%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20her%20training%2C%20Asha%2C%20along%20with%20her%20regiment%2C%20set%20out%20on%20foot%20to%20march%20from%20Bangkok%20to%20the%20far%20off%20Burma%20(present-day%20Myanmar)%20in%201945.%20Amid%20bombings%2C%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20armed%20force%20remained%20adamant%20as%20they%20sang%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKadam%20Kadam%20Badhaye%20Ja%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20the%20regimental%20quick%20march%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20regiment%20managed%20to%20reach%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Irrawaddy%20River%20%E2%80%94%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20largest%20river%20and%20most%20important%20commercial%20waterway%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20flooded.%20This%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20them%20to%20cross%20the%20river%20and%20join%20the%20major%20INA%20army%20on%20the%20other%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20regiment%20set%20their%20camps%20on%20the%20bank.%20However%2C%20they%20were%20attacked%20by%20the%20British%20and%20put%20behind%20bars%20for%20over%20a%20month.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20forced%20to%20retreat%20to%20Bangkok.%20While%20all%20the%20other%20women%20went%20back%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20%3Cem%3Edadi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(grandma)%20had%20nowhere%20to%20go.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20her%20father%2C%20who%20wa